title: Apply for a refugee integration loan

heading_context: Apply for a refugee integration loan
chunks.html_content:
Apply for a loan if you’re one of the following:

  • a refugee
  • you have humanitarian protection
  • a dependant of a refugee or someone with humanitarian protection

You must be over 18 to use this service.
chunks.plain_content:

  a refugee
  you have humanitarian protection
  a dependant of a refugee or someone with humanitarian protection

heading_context: Apply for a refugee integration loan
chunks.html_content: Before you apply, check what you can use the loan for and how much you can borrow.
chunks.plain_content:
Apply for a refugee integration loan
Before you apply, check what you can use the loan for and how much you can borrow.

heading_context: Apply for a refugee integration loan
chunks.html_content:
Make sure you have your:

  • biometric residence permit (BRP)
  • National Insurance number
  • Home Office reference number - you can find this on your asylum application letter
  • bank account or building society details

If you’re making a joint application with your partner, you’ll also need their BRP details and National Insurance number.

If you need help with your application or filling in the form, you can contact your local refugee community organisation.

You can also contact the integration loan team.
